-- slug: how-many-calories-in-pizza
INSERT INTO public.blog_posts
  (slug, title, meta_description, featured_image_url, content, status, is_published, language, published_at, created_at, updated_at)
VALUES
  (
    'how-many-calories-in-pizza',
    'How Many Calories in Pizza? Complete Nutrition Guide',
    'Discover exactly how many calories are in pizza. Compare Domino',
    'https://smsikaqybxtnzjvruhsa.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/blog-images/compressed-1767905734948.webp',
    '<div><h1>How Many Calories in Pizza? Complete Nutrition Guide</h1><p>Pizza is one of the world''s most beloved foods. Whether you grab a quick slice for lunch, order delivery for movie night, or make homemade pizza with family, knowing the calorie content helps you make smarter choices while still enjoying this comfort food.</p><p>In this guide, we''ll break down how many calories are in different types of pizza, compare popular pizza chains, and share tips for enjoying pizza while managing your calorie intake.</p><hr><h2>Average Calories in a Slice of Pizza</h2><p>Pizza calories vary depending on size, crust, toppings, and preparation method. Here''s a general overview:</p><p>Pizza Type Calories per Slice Plain cheese pizza (thin Crust) 180-220 Plain cheese pizza (regular crust): 220-280 Plain cheese pizza (deep dish) 300-400 Pepperoni pizza 250-320 Meat lovers pizza 320-400 Veggie pizza: 200-260 Margherita pizza: 200-250 BBQ chicken pizza 280-350</p><p>A typical slice is approximately 1/8 of a 14-inch pizza.</p><hr><h2>What Affects Pizza Calories?</h2><p>Knowing what adds to your pizza''s calorie count can help you make smarter choices. Let''s break it down:</p><h3>The Crust</h3><p>Crust Type Calories (per slice base) Thin Crust 120-150 Regular hand-tossed 150-200, pan/deep dish 200-280 Stuffed crust: 250-350 Cauliflower crust: 80-120 Gluten-free Crust: 140-180</p><p>The crust can account for 40-60% of your slice''s calories. Choosing thin crust over deep dish can save 100-150 calories per slice.</p><h3>The Cheese</h3><p>Cheese Amount Calories Added Light cheese 50-70 Regular cheese 80-110 Extra cheese: 120-160 Double cheese: 160-220</p><p>Mozzarella is the standard pizzMozzarella is the standard pizza cheese at about 85 calories per ounce. Requesting light cheese can reduce calories.slice) Marinara (tomato) 10-20 White garlic sauce 50-80 BBQ sauce 25-40 Alfredo sauce 60-90 Olive oil base 40-60 Pesto 50-70</p><p>Traditional tomato-based marinara sauce is the lowest-calorie option.</p><h3>The Toppings</h3><p>Topping Calories Added (per slice) Pepperoni 30-50 Italian sausage 40-60 Bacon 35-50 Ham15-25 Grilled chicken 20-30 Ground beef 40-55 Mushrooms: 3-5 Onions: 3-5 Bell peppers: 3-5 Olives: 10-15 Jalapeños 2-4 Pineapple: 10-15 Spinach: 2-3 Tomatoes: 3-5 Anchovies: 15-20</p><p>Vegetables add minimal calories, while meat toppings increase the count.</p><hr><h2>Popular Pizza Chain Calories Compared</h2><p><em>Note: All nutritional information is sourced from official company websites. Values may vary by location and preparation method. All trademarks belong to their respective owners. This comparison is for educational purposes only.</em></p><h3>Domino''s Pizza</h3><p>Pizza (1 slice, large) Calories: Cheese (Hand Tossed) 290, Pepperoni (Hand Tossed) 313, MeatZZa 350, Pacific Veggie 280, Buffalo Chicken 300, ExtravaganZZa 360, Cheese (Thin Crust) 215, Cheese (Brooklyn Style) 245</p><h3>Pizza Hut</h3><p>Pizza (1 slice, large) Calories: Cheese (Hand Tossed) 300, Pepperoni (Hand Tossed) 330 Meat Lover''s 410 Supreme 340 Veggie Lover''s 280 Cheese (Thin ''N Crispy) 240 Cheese (Pan) 350 Cheese (Stuffed Crust) 390</p><h3>Papa John''s</h3><p>Pizza (1 slice, large) Calories: Cheese (Original) 290 Pepperoni (Original) 320 The Works 330 Garden Fresh 260 The Meats 370 Cheese (Thin Crust) 230</p><h3>Little Caesars</h3><p>Pizza (1 slice, large) Calories: Classic Cheese 250, Pepperoni 280, Meat Treat 320, Veggie 240, Extra Most Bestest Pepperoni 350</p><h3>Papa Murphy''s</h3><p>Pizza (1 slice, large) Calories: Cheese (Original) 270, Pepperoni 300, Cowboy 350, Gourmet Vegetarian 260, Chicken Bacon Artichoke 310</p><h3>Costco</h3><p>Pizza (1 slice) Calories: Cheese 700, Pepperoni 720, Combo 680</p><p><em>Note: Costco slices are significantly larger than standard pizza chain slices.</em></p><hr><h2>Calories by Pizza Style</h2><p>Different pizza styles from around the world have varying calorie contents:</p><h3>New York Style</h3><p>TypeCalories per SlicePlain cheese250-300 Pepperoni 300-350, white pizza 320-380</p><p>New York style features large, foldable slices with a thin, crispy crust.</p><h3>Chicago Deep Dish</h3><p>TypeCalories per SliceCheese400-500Sausage480-580Spinach420-480</p><p>Deep-dish pizza has more calories because of the thick, buttery crust and extra cheese.</p><h3>Neapolitan (Italian)</h3><p>Type Calories per Pizza Margherita 600-800 Marinara 500-650, Quattro Formaggi 800-950</p><p>Traditional Neapolitan pizzas are personal-sized (10-12 inches) and meant for one.</p><h3>Detroit Style</h3><p>TypeCalories per SliceCheese 280-350 Pepperoni 320-400</p><p>Rectangular pan pizza with crispy, cheesy edges.</p><h3>Sicilian</h3><p>Type of Calories per Slice: Cheese 300-380, Pepperoni 350-430</p><p>Thick, spongy crust baked in a rectangular pan.</p><hr><h2>Frozen Pizza Calories</h2><p>If you prefer cooking at home, here''s how popular frozen pizzas compare:</p><p>Brand &amp; Type Calories (1/4 pizza) DiGiorno Rising Crust Pepperoni 380 DiGiorno Thin Crust Four Cheese 290 Red Baron Classic Pepperoni 370 Totino''s Party Pizza 340 Newman''s Own Margherita 280, California Pizza Kitchen BBQ Chicken 320 Amy''s Cheese (Organic) 290, Freschetta Pepperoni 360</p><hr><h2>Low-Calorie Pizza Options</h2><p>If you''re watching calories, consider these alternatives:</p><h3>Best Low-Calorie Choices</h3><p>OptionCalories Cauliflower crust cheese pizza: 150-200/slice Thin Crust veggie pizza: 180-220/slice Portobello mushroom "pizza" 150-180 English muffin pizza 180-220 Pita bread pizza 200-250 Zucchini pizza bites: 80-100 (4 pieces)</p><h3>Tips for Reducing Pizza Calories</h3><p>Choose thin crust over thick, pan, Choose thin crust over thick, pan, or stuffed crust to save 80-150 calories per slice. Ask for light or half cheese to reduce calories by 40-60 per slice. Load up on vegetable toppings like mushrooms, peppers, onions, and spinach. Skip meat or choose lean options like grilled chicken instead of pepperoni or sausage. Avoid stuffed-crust and cheese-filled options. Choose tomato-based sauce over creamy white or Alfredo sauces. Blot excess oil with a napkin to remove 20-40 calories per slice. The number of pizza slices depends on your daily calorie needs:</p><p>Daily Calorie Goal: Recommended Slices 1,500 calories 1-2 slices, 2,000 calories 2-3 slices, 2,500 calories 3-4 slices</p><p>Remember to account for sides like breadsticks, wings, or soda, which can add 200-600 calories.</p><hr><h2>Pizza vs Other Fast Foods</h2><p>How does pizza compare to other popular fast food options?</p><p>Food Calories 2 slices cheese pizza 500-560 Big Mac 550, Whopper with cheese 660 Chipotle burrito: 1,000+ Subway 6" Italian BMT: 410 KFC 3-piece meal: 780 Taco Bell Crunchwrap Supreme: 530</p><p>Pizza can be a reasonable choice with portion control.</p><hr><h2>Making Healthier Pizza at Home</h2><p>Homemade pizza gHomemade pizza gives you control over ingredients and portions: es (whole personal pizza: Whole wheat thin crust, light cheese, veggies 400-500 Cauliflower crust, regular cheese, chicken 450-550 Naan bread pizza with veggies 350-450 Portobello cap pizza 200-300</p><hr><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How many calories are in a whole pizza?</h3><p>A whole large cheese pizza (14 inches, eight slices) contains approximately 1,800-2,400 calories, depending on the crust type and toppings.</p><h3>Is pizza healthier than a burger?</h3><p>It depends on portions. Two slices of cheese pizza (about 500 calories) are comparable to a regular cheeseburger. However, pizza provides more calcium from cheese, while burgers offer more protein.</p><h3>Can I eat pizza on a diet?</h3><p>Yes! Choose thin crust, load up on veggies, go light on cheese, and limit yourself to 1-2 slices. Pair with a side salad instead of breadsticks or wings.</p><h3>What''s the lowest-calorie pizza at Domino''s?</h3><p>The Pacific Veggie on thin crust is one of the lowest options at approximately 180 calories per slice.</p><h3>How many calories are in a Costco pizza slice?</h3><p>Costco pizza slices are notably large, containing approximately 700-720 calories per slice, which is equivalent to 2-3 regular pizza slices.</p><h3>Is cauliflower-crust pizza actually healthier?</h3><p>Cauliflower crust typically has 30-50% fewer carbs and calories than regular crust. However, some store-bought versions add extra ingredients that increase calories, so always check the label.</p><hr><h2>Track Your Pizza Calories with CalorieVision</h2><p>Want to know exactly how many calories are in your pizza? CalorieVision''s AI-powered photo analysis can instantly calculate the calories in any pizza, whether it''s homemade, from your favorite restaurant, or frozen. Snap a photo and get accurate nutritional information in seconds!</p><p><strong>Try CalorieVision free</strong> and take the guesswork out of tracking your pizza calories.</p><hr><h2>Conclusion</h2><p>Pizza calories can range from 180 to 700 per slice, depending on the style, crust, cheese, and toppings. The key to enjoying pizza while managing calories is making informed choices: opt for thin crust, choose vegetable toppings, go easy on the cheese, and practice portion control.</p><p>Remember, pizza can absolutely fit into a balanced diet. The key is awareness and moderation. Now that you know exactly how many calories are in your favorite pizzas, you can make choices that align with your health goals without sacrificing the foods you love.</p></div>',
    'published',
    true,
    'en',
    '2026-01-04T14:49:05.815+00:00',
    '2026-01-04T14:49:05.815+00:00',
    '2026-01-04T14:49:05.815+00:00'
  )
